1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,880
Half the things in this shop never got a barcode.

2
00:00:03,260 --> 00:00:08,740
Loose herbs, jars, lighters, and a cream that cost 40 francs.

3
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:11,740
It's Saturday, the new kid's on the till.

4
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:15,580
A customer wants the 40 franc cream.

5
00:00:16,340 --> 00:00:18,940
She reaches for the scanner out of habit and stops.

6
00:00:19,860 --> 00:00:21,200
There's nothing to scan.

7
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:24,120
The factory never gave it a barcode.

8
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:28,640
And on the shelf, five tubes, nearly identical.

9
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:32,380
One's 40 francs, one's 12, guess wrong?

10
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,820
And the cash drawer never balances.

11
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:40,600
On an old till, that cream is a price typed by hand,

12
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:44,780
a sticky note on the monitor, a number she has to remember,

13
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:51,280
or call the manager again every unmarked item, a tiny gamble.

14
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:54,800
And the head shop is full of them.

15
00:00:55,540 --> 00:00:56,600
She doesn't scan.

16
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,520
She opens the catalog and there it is,

17
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:04,640
wearing its own face — a photo, the name, 40 francs.

18
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:11,520
She taps the picture into the cart, right price, first try.

19
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:14,320
No sticky notes, no manager.

20
00:01:15,660 --> 00:01:19,620
Because the first time this cream was ever sold,

21
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:23,620
someone gave it a face, a quick photo at the counter,

22
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:30,500
born once and from that moment, anyone can sell it by sight.

23
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:34,060
That's the trick the big chains miss.

24
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,500
A barcode belongs to the factory,

25
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:44,120
a picture belongs to you, your shelf, your goods, your eyes.

26
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:49,500
Banco doesn't make you label the world before you sell it.

27
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,680
You sell what you can see.

28
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,920
Born once, known by heart.
